remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoderFrame` pairs a <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> with a `TimeSpan` duration to
describe one frame in an animated WebP file. Pass an array (or span) of frames to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(System.ReadOnlySpan{SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame},SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions)>
or one of its overloads.

This is a value type and does not require disposal, though the underlying
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> it references must remain valid for the lifetime of the frame.

## Examples

```csharp
using var bmp1 = SKBitmap.Decode("frame1.png");
using var bmp2 = SKBitmap.Decode("frame2.png");

var frames = new SKWebpEncoderFrame[]
{
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bmp1, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
    new SKWebpEncoderFrame(bmp2, TimeSpan.FromMilliseconds(100)),
};

var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated(frames, options);
if (data is not null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("animated.webp", data.ToArray());
```
